<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>ghstatsussy hosted</title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;500;600&family=IBM+Plex+Sans:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
    <style>
      :root {
        --bg-0: #08111d;
        --bg-1: #0d1727;
        --panel: rgba(10, 17, 30, 0.82);
        --panel-strong: rgba(9, 15, 26, 0.94);
        --line: rgba(142, 194, 255, 0.13);
        --line-strong: rgba(142, 194, 255, 0.28);
        --ink: #e9f3ff;
        --muted: #8ea4bc;
        --cyan: #5ad8ff;
        --lime: #9ff5a4;
        --amber: #f2b15d;
        --coral: #ff8573;
        --shadow: 0 30px 90px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.42);
        --radius-xl: 30px;
        --radius-lg: 22px;
        --radius-md: 16px;
      }

      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      body {
        margin: 0;
        min-height: 100vh;
        color: var(--ink);
        font-family: "IBM Plex Sans", sans-serif;
        background:
          radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(90, 216, 255, 0.18), transparent 26%),
          radial-gradient(circle at right, rgba(159, 245, 164, 0.08), transparent 20%),
          linear-gradient(160deg, #07101a 0%, #0a1320 48%, #0d1727 100%);
        position: relative;
        overflow-x: hidden;
      }

      body::before,
      body::after {
        content: "";
        position: fixed;
        inset: 0;
        pointer-events: none;
      }

      body::before {
        background-image:
          linear-gradient(var(--line) 1px, transparent 1px),
          linear-gradient(90deg, var(--line) 1px, transparent 1px);
        background-size: 36px 36px;
        opacity: 0.7;
      }

      body::after {
        background:
          linear-gradient(90deg, transparent 0%, rgba(90, 216, 255, 0.06) 50%, transparent 100%);
        transform: translateX(-35%);
        animation: drift 12s linear infinite;
        opacity: 0.4;
      }

      .shell {
        width: min(1220px, calc(100% - 28px));
        margin: 28px auto 36px;
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
      }

      .eyebrow,
      .kicker,
      .pill,
      .micro,
      .stat-label {
        font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", monospace;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      }

      .hero {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1.2fr 0.88fr;
        gap: 18px;
      }

      .panel {
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
        background: var(--panel);
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
        box-shadow: var(--shadow);
        backdrop-filter: blur(18px);
      }

      .panel::before {
        content: "";
        position: absolute;
        inset: 0;
        background:
          linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(90, 216, 255, 0.08), transparent 42%),
          linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02), transparent 38%);
        pointer-events: none;
      }

      .hero-copy {
        padding: 32px;
        display: grid;
        gap: 22px;
        min-height: 640px;
      }

      .eyebrow {
        display: inline-flex;
        width: fit-content;
        padding: 9px 12px;
        border: 1px solid rgba(90, 216, 255, 0.25);
        border-radius: 999px;
        color: var(--cyan);
        font-size: 12px;
      }

      h1,
      h2,
      h3,
      p {
        margin: 0;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: clamp(2.8rem, 6vw, 5.8rem);
        line-height: 0.92;
        max-width: 10ch;
      }

      .lede {
        max-width: 56ch;
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 1.08rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
      }

      .hero-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
        gap: 14px;
        margin-top: auto;
      }

      .metric-card,
      .signal-card,
      .note,
      .callout,
      .timeline {
        background: var(--panel-strong);
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
      }

      .metric-card {
        padding: 16px;
      }

      .stat-label {
        font-size: 11px;
        color: var(--muted);
      }

      .metric-card strong {
        display: block;
        margin-top: 10px;
        font-size: 2rem;
      }

      .hero-side {
        display: grid;
        gap: 18px;
      }

      .signal-card {
        padding: 24px;
        min-height: 400px;
        display: grid;
        gap: 18px;
      }

      .signal-header,
      .note-header,
      .timeline-row,
      .callout-grid {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 12px;
      }

      .chart-frame {
        position: relative;
        height: 220px;
        border-radius: 18px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        background:
          linear-gradient(var(--line) 1px, transparent 1px),
          linear-gradient(90deg, var(--line) 1px, transparent 1px),
          linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(90, 216, 255, 0.12), rgba(90, 216, 255, 0.02));
        background-size: 28px 28px, 28px 28px, 100% 100%;
        overflow: hidden;
      }

      .chart-line,
      .chart-line-2 {
        position: absolute;
        inset: 0;
      }

      .chart-line svg,
      .chart-line-2 svg {
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
      }

      .chart-line path {
        stroke: var(--cyan);
        stroke-width: 3;
        fill: rgba(90, 216, 255, 0.12);
      }

      .chart-line-2 path {
        stroke: var(--lime);
        stroke-width: 2;
        fill: none;
        stroke-dasharray: 8 8;
      }

      .radar {
        position: absolute;
        inset: 0;
        background: radial-gradient(circle at 18% 70%, rgba(159, 245, 164, 0.14), transparent 18%);
        animation: pulse 4s ease-in-out infinite;
      }

      .note,
      .callout,
      .timeline {
        padding: 18px;
      }

      .note p,
      .callout p,
      .timeline p,
      .muted {
        color: var(--muted);
      }

      .cta {
        display: inline-flex;
        justify-content: center;
        align-items: center;
        padding: 14px 18px;
        border-radius: 16px;
        text-decoration: none;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: #07101a;
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--cyan), var(--lime));
        box-shadow: 0 12px 32px rgba(90, 216, 255, 0.2);
      }

      .cta:hover {
        transform: translateY(-1px);
      }

      .timeline {
        display: grid;
        gap: 12px;
      }

      .timeline-row {
        align-items: flex-start;
      }

      .dot {
        width: 10px;
        height: 10px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        background: var(--cyan);
        margin-top: 5px;
        box-shadow: 0 0 0 8px rgba(90, 216, 255, 0.08);
      }

      .dot.lime {
        background: var(--lime);
        box-shadow: 0 0 0 8px rgba(159, 245, 164, 0.08);
      }

      .dot.amber {
        background: var(--amber);
        box-shadow: 0 0 0 8px rgba(242, 177, 93, 0.08);
      }

      .pill {
        display: inline-flex;
        width: fit-content;
        padding: 8px 10px;
        font-size: 11px;
        color: var(--amber);
        border: 1px solid rgba(242, 177, 93, 0.25);
        border-radius: 999px;
      }

      code {
        font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", monospace;
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
        padding: 2px 6px;
        border-radius: 8px;
      }

      @keyframes drift {
        from { transform: translateX(-35%); }
        to { transform: translateX(35%); }
      }

      @keyframes pulse {
        0%, 100% { opacity: 0.35; transform: scale(0.98); }
        50% { opacity: 0.8; transform: scale(1.03); }
      }

      @media (max-width: 980px) {
        .hero {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }

        .hero-copy {
          min-height: auto;
        }
      }

      @media (max-width: 640px) {
        .shell {
          width: min(100% - 18px, 1220px);
          margin: 18px auto 24px;
        }

        .hero-copy,
        .signal-card,
        .note,
        .callout,
        .timeline {
          padding: 18px;
        }

        .hero-grid {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main class="shell">
      <section class="hero">
        <article class="panel hero-copy">
          <span class="eyebrow">Blueprint Atlas / hosted GitHub infographics</span>
          <div>
            <h1>Plot your GitHub signal, then give it a clean little URL.</h1>
            <p class="lede">`ghstatsussy` turns your contribution history into a shareable HTML report with a calmer privacy posture: GitHub OAuth stays server-side, private-activity reports stay private, and metadata retention is optional instead of assumed.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="hero-grid">
            <section class="metric-card">
              <div class="stat-label">Identity</div>
              <strong>GitHub OAuth</strong>
              <div class="muted">Sign in once, generate on demand.</div>
            </section>
            <section class="metric-card">
              <div class="stat-label">Artifact</div>
              <strong>Hosted HTML</strong>
              <div class="muted">Self-contained report snapshots, not a live dashboard leak.</div>
            </section>
            <section class="metric-card">
              <div class="stat-label">Share shape</div>
              <strong>/r/slug</strong>
              <div class="muted">Or `username.ghstats.ussyco.de` when a public report exists.</div>
            </section>
            <section class="metric-card">
              <div class="stat-label">Retention</div>
              <strong>Opt-in metadata</strong>
              <div class="muted">HTML by default. Extra metadata only if you ask for it.</div>
            </section>
          </div>
        </article>

        <aside class="hero-side">
          <section class="signal-card">
            <div class="signal-header">
              <div>
                <div class="micro muted">Activity map</div>
                <h2>From repos to report</h2>
              </div>
              <span class="pill">privacy-first hosted mode</span>
            </div>

            <div class="chart-frame" aria-hidden="true">
              <div class="radar"></div>
              <div class="chart-line">
                <svg viewBox="0 0 100 100" preserveAspectRatio="none">
                  <path d="M0,82 L12,74 L22,68 L34,52 L46,60 L59,40 L72,46 L86,18 L100,28 L100,100 L0,100 Z"></path>
                </svg>
              </div>
              <div class="chart-line-2">
                <svg viewBox="0 0 100 100" preserveAspectRatio="none">
                  <path d="M0,68 L16,66 L28,58 L41,62 L54,34 L70,37 L83,30 L100,12"></path>
                </svg>
              </div>
            </div>

            <section class="timeline">
              <div class="timeline-row">
                <div class="dot"></div>
                <div>
                  <div class="micro muted">Step 01</div>
                  <strong>Sign in with GitHub</strong>
                  <p>Use your normal GitHub account to authorize the hosted app.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="timeline-row">
                <div class="dot lime"></div>
                <div>
                  <div class="micro muted">Step 02</div>
                  <strong>Choose your window</strong>
                  <p>Generate a `30d`, `12w`, or `6m` snapshot and decide whether metadata is retained.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="timeline-row">
                <div class="dot amber"></div>
                <div>
                  <div class="micro muted">Step 03</div>
                  <strong>Share the result</strong>
                  <p>Publish with a slug link or let your user host serve the latest public report.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>
          </section>

          <section class="callout panel" style="padding: 22px;">
            <div class="callout-grid">
              <div>
                <div class="micro muted">Ready when you are</div>
                <h3>Bring your GitHub account</h3>
              </div>
              <a class="cta" href="/auth/github/login">Sign in with GitHub</a>
            </div>
            <p class="lede" style="font-size: 1rem; margin-top: 14px; max-width: none;">Sign in with GitHub, choose a time window, and generate a polished stats page you can share. By default, ghstatsussy keeps only the hosted HTML report; metadata retention is optional, and reports with private activity stay private.</p>
          </section>
        </aside>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
